cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.PF, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with TCP flows passing through a multi-hop network and analyzes their performance. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper involves computing steady state throughput for different TCP flows. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possibility as the paper may involve analyzing the security of the network. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is another possibility as the paper deals with performance analysis of TCP flows. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper involves an optimization program to approximate the steady state throughput of different flows.
